            <article class="mb-6">
                <h3 class="text-base sm:text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">What is Bikram Sambat?</h3>
                <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm md:text-base text-gray-600">
                    Bikram Sambat (BS) is the official calendar of Nepal, approximately 56 years, 8 months, and 15 days ahead of the Gregorian calendar (AD). This tool accurately converts dates between BS (1970-2100) and AD (1913-2043), ensuring compatibility for scheduling, events, and official records in Nepal.
                </p>
            </article>
            <article class="mb-6">
                <h3 class="text-base sm:text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Tips and Tricks for Date Conversion</h3>
                <ul class="example-list text-xs sm:text-sm md:text-base text-gray-600">
                    <li><strong>Valid date ranges:</strong> Use BS years 1970-2100 or AD years 1913-2043 for accurate conversions. For example, 2082/01/01 BS converts to 2025/04/14 AD (Monday).</li>
                    <li><strong>Month names:</strong> Select the correct month (e.g., Baisakh for BS, January for AD) to align with the calendar system. The tool handles month-day variations in BS.</li>
                    <li><strong>Day validation:</strong> Ensure the day is valid (1-32 for BS, 1-31 for AD, depending on the month). Invalid dates will trigger an error message.</li>
                    <li><strong>Copy for use:</strong> Copy the converted date (e.g., '2025 April 14, Monday') for use in documents, calendars, or planning tools.</li>
                    <li><strong>Clear for new conversions:</strong> Use the "Clear" button to reset the form when switching between BS and AD conversions.</li>
